Reasoning: The paper focuses on studying large-scale article access data of the English Wikipedia to compare articles with respect to the two main paradigms of information seeking, i.e., search by formulating a query, and navigation by following hyperlinks. This involves analyzing network, content, and editing activity features, as well as modeling access behavior. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval), followed by cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.SD (Software Engineering), cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction), and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
